{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddccfe9fb-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s2263"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2263"},"text":"§ 2263.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Enforcement of temporary cease and desist orders","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of violation or threatened violation of, or failure to obey, a temporary cease and desist order issued under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s2262"},"text":"section 2262 of this title","children":[],"tail":", the Farm Credit Administration may apply to the United States district court, or the United States court of any territory, within the jurisdiction of which the home office of the institution is located, for an injunction to enforce such order, and, if the court shall determine that there has been such violation or threatened violation or failure to obey, it shall be the duty of the court to issue such injunction."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddccfe9fc-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/181/tV/s5"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–181, title V, § 5","children":[],"tail":".27, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/205/tII/s204"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–205, title II, § 204","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 1985","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/99/1696"},"text":"99 Stat. 1696","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddccfe9fd-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddccfe9fe-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{